Guess MS wants everything in the cloud, so shadow copy is out, well almost.<br />If I recall they were going to cut out system image part of it, but luckily they left it in.<br />I backed up once a month and was a great help with stubborn virus/whatnots. Saved me a number of times.<br />Stopped using it about half a year ago, as antivirus software much better, or websites cleaner these days.<br />Probably would not have helped in this case, backup gaps too long.<br /><br />You are right GauravK, about the &quot;File History&quot; function. Got home turned on computer, checked a desktop skin file. I had left computer on for hours the night before, for it to do its thing. <br />Still saving, huh? I had originally plugged in a 128 gb drive, and even after formatting, said it can not use that drive, choose another drive. Put the 32 gb in. Not impressed so far. Will switch to a usb 3.00 speed to see if that works. Do I have to buy another same size hard drive, just for it to work? Holy moley.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=856">juniper7</a> — Fri Nov 07, 2014 7:32 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
