Thanks for caring Jcee.<br /><br />I saw that webpage before too, after the fact. Tried a few programs that worked before for deletions, Recuva, Easeus, usually the best, Photorec. None helped this time for overwritten file. Yep. Win 8 ripped out Previous Version feature and gave File History instead. Never even knew how to use it, until seeing that wikiHow page. <br />I may have overwritten a few other times before for other skins, wondering &quot;I thought I made that change already?&quot; Does Reshacker put an older version if it crashes?&quot; Now I know, it was me all along messing it up <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_lol.gif" alt=":lol:" title="Laughing" /> <br />It's over now. Spent long enough looking. The skin wasn't that great anyway. Got to stop making big skins with 20 option buttons. I'm going to redu and break up the skin into probably 3 or 4 mini skins instead. Diversify for better security <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" />.  <br /><br />I plugged in a 32 gig usb drive at back of computer, and set up for File History use. Taking forever for it saving copies. Will see if File History is any good with a test on weekend.<br /><br />Thanks.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=856">juniper7</a> — Thu Nov 06, 2014 8:29 pm</p><hr />
